# Append-only registries: both sides' added lines should concatenate, not
# conflict. git's built-in `union` merge driver auto-resolves these, removing
# the most repetitive hand-resolution step during integration.
#
# NOT for files with in-place edits (e.g. CATALOG.tsv has per-row status
# edits that union would duplicate) — only genuinely append-only files.
#
# seams-init is NOT append-only: installing a seam DELETES its
# CONTRACT_RECONCILE_PENDING allowlist entry (and may add/remove init_all
# lines), so `merge=union` silently DROPS the deletions of whichever side it
# does not keep — repeatedly reddening main on the recurrence guards. Both
# crates/seams-init/src/lib.rs and crates/seams-init/Cargo.toml therefore use
# the NORMAL 3-way merge driver: divergence becomes a LOUD conflict that forces
# explicit union-of-init_all + union-of-allowlist resolution by hand.
# DESIGN_DEBT.md IS genuinely append-only and keeps merge=union.
DESIGN_DEBT.md                 merge=union
